text.tspan: Simplex is the first VR-Native CAD tool

flowRoot.flowPara: VR is an entirely new visual medium that seems ideal for interactive 3D design. However, current 3D interfaces are dependent on hotkeys, popup menus, dialog boxes, and cursors that live on 2D planes. We don't think rendering all this 2D stuff on floating rectangles is the right way to translate 3D CAD into VR. We can do better than that.

Simplex is an experiment in adapting what we know about effective 3D design tools into VR. Direct 3D tracking is a huge win, but in a design tool you'll still need efficient scene navigation controls and accurate 3D manipulation tools. And sometimes you'll still need to use numbers or enter text. Simplex is where we are going to figure all this out.

We think that 3D designers are still going to be sitting most of the time, so we've focused on a seated experience designed for use with a mouse. But we support the XBox One gamepad as well, so you can stand up if you like. And we'll be adding direct 3D spatial input soon.
